Files under `src/vendor/` are derived from KeyPeek:

  - `layout_key.rs`, `keycode_labels/` — QMK/VIA keycode-label tables + model;
  - `protocols/` — VIA, Vial, and ZMK HID/Studio protocol code, plus the
    KLE/QMK-JSON/geometry parsers;
  - `zmk_keycode_labels/` — ZMK behavior/HID-usage label tables;
  - `device_discovery.rs` — HID/serial/BLE device discovery + classification,
    with KeyPeek's own unit tests (the project's only test suite).

They are reused and reshaped for Keyplane under the terms of the GPL-3.0.
Modifications from upstream are noted in `src/vendor/mod.rs`:

  - module paths rehomed under `crate::vendor::*`;
  - icon-font glyphs (egui_phosphor) replaced with plain-text labels via
    `glyphs.rs`, dropping the egui/eframe UI dependency (Keyplane renders in a
    web frontend);
  - a `read_all_raw` method added to the `KeyboardProtocol` trait so Keyplane
    keeps raw VIA keycodes and derives Semantic Actions itself.

The rest of Keyplane is likewise GPL-3.0-only; see the repository LICENSE.
